### Knowledge Graph
{% if knowledge_graph_backend == 'neo4j' %}

Start Neo4j via the Compose `knowledge-graph` profile:

```bash
{{ container_runtime }} compose --profile knowledge-graph up -d neo4j
```

Open the Neo4j Browser at `http://localhost:7474` to run Cypher queries
interactively. The adapter in `backend/src/{{ project_slug }}/ai/knowledge_graph/neo4j_adapter.py`
uses the async Bolt driver (`neo4j.AsyncGraphDatabase`).

Common Cypher patterns used by the adapter:

```cypher
-- Add a relationship
MERGE (s:Entity {name: $subject})
MERGE (o:Entity {name: $object})
MERGE (s)-[r:RELATION {type: $predicate}]->(o)

-- Bulk insert via UNWIND
UNWIND $triplets AS t
MERGE (s:Entity {name: t.subject})
MERGE (o:Entity {name: t.object})
MERGE (s)-[r:RELATION {type: t.predicate}]->(o)

-- Query neighbors by depth
MATCH (s:Entity {name: $entity})-[r*1..2]-(neighbor:Entity)
RETURN DISTINCT neighbor.name AS entity

-- Filtered query with parameters
MATCH (s:Entity)-[r:RELATION]->(o:Entity)
WHERE s.name = $subject AND r.type = $predicate
RETURN o.name AS object

-- Count all entities
MATCH (e:Entity) RETURN count(e) AS cnt

-- Delete all graph data
MATCH (n) DETACH DELETE n
```

The adapter uses `:Entity` as the node label and `:RELATION` with a
`type` property as the edge label. All queries are parameterized to
prevent injection.

To tear down the graph data without removing the service:

```bash
{{ container_runtime }} compose --profile knowledge-graph exec neo4j cypher-shell -u neo4j -p changeme "MATCH (n) DETACH DELETE n"
```
{% elif knowledge_graph_backend == 'rdflib' %}

The RDFLib backend (`backend/src/{{ project_slug }}/ai/knowledge_graph/rdflib_adapter.py`) stores
triples in-process. It supports persistence to Turtle (`.ttl`) files
and read-only SPARQL queries via `sparql_query()`.
{% else %}

The NetworkX backend (`backend/src/{{ project_slug }}/ai/knowledge_graph/networkx_adapter.py`) stores
the graph in-process using `networkx.DiGraph`. It supports JSON
persistence and is the default for local development.
{% endif %}
