### Workflow Checkpointers

LangGraph workflows store execution state in a checkpointer. During
development, the in-memory checkpointer is used by default (no
persistence across restarts). To test durable workflows locally,
switch to the SQLite checkpointer:

```bash
export {{ project_slug | upper }}_CHECKPOINTER_BACKEND=sqlite
```

The SQLite checkpoint file (`.langgraph_checkpoints.db`) is
created in the project root. Inspect it with:

```bash
sqlite3 .langgraph_checkpoints.db ".tables"
sqlite3 .langgraph_checkpoints.db "SELECT * FROM checkpoints LIMIT 5;"
```

Reset checkpoint state by deleting the file:

```bash
rm -f .langgraph_checkpoints.db
```
